<p> </p>
<p><span><strong><i>* During “online” days, there will be no live meeting.  Instead you will be required to participate on the discussion board throughout the week.  There will be no specific time where you need to be online during these weeks, so you can work at your leisure and pace.  All the information you will need for these online weeks will be available on the website at least one week prior.  </i></strong></span></p>
<p><span><strong><i></i></strong></span></p>
<p><span><strong><i></i></strong></span></p>
<p><span><strong>Participation:  </strong>Participation is integral in this course.  Whether it be during the class webcast, or on discussion boards, you are required to be an active member of this experience.  You will be given plenty of opportunities to share your thoughts.</span></p>
<p> </p>
<p><span><strong>Online Quizzes:  </strong>There will be a few online quizzes throughout the semester, based on the textbook material.   The quizzes will be timed, however you will always have a window of one week to start your quiz.  They are not during class time.  </span></p>
<p> </p>
<p><span><strong>Midterm:  </strong>The midterm exam will be a timed, online exam.   It will cover textbook material up to chapter 9.  The format will be multiple choice, true-false, and fill-in-the-blank. <strong> </strong></span></p>
<p> </p>
<p><span><strong>Case Studies:  </strong>Case Studies will be discussed in further detail during the first week of the course.  Cases will be both individual and group.  The case studies will vary in length and detail.  </span></p>
<p> </p>
<p><span><strong>Semester Project:  </strong>You and your group will be tasked with bringing a new company, product, or service to the Cambridge, MA market.  There will be discussion of this project in detail during weeks 2 and 3.  </span></p>
<p> </p>
<p><span><strong>Final Exam:  </strong>The final exam will be during the 12/18 class.  It will be live and timed.  You will receive more information regarding this exam during the first two weeks of the course.   </span></p>
